The containment procedures are a total waste, you could have done a lot more to set up the article. As it stands they're rather perfunctory and are basically a waste of space. The description is acceptable but doesn't really do anything amazing beyond setting up the log. The log itself and the final note are visceral and gripping by the end. The note-at-the-end cliche is about as worn out as cliche's get but I'll be damned if it doesn't work here. +1 for pulling that off. The brevity makes it work overall, I think.








Whether you like it or not, history is on our side. We will bury you!






