13 Dec 2019 15:28






First and foremost, +1 for the twist. Excellent concept, well delivered, didn't overstay it's welcome. I do have to agree with Roget and Rounder on this though.

The containment procedures do very little to lead the mystery, and don't really function. If we haven't figured out how to kill these animals, humanely or otherwise, then this is a much bigger issue warranting greater response. As it stands, this feels like  would have made this feel more complete. A unique method of eliminating these animals using anomalous, or just Foundation level technology would have closed the loop as well without subtracting from the story.

The dialogue feels stilted, unprofessional, and lacks a cohesive tone. You also go a bit too hard on the accent with  would have had much more weight if these agents had started off by-the-books, then having that broken by the horror of the situation. The good part is the actual skeleton is strong: the shock of the dog not dying after multiple gunshots is well executed and paced.

It's still a +1 for sure, but it needs to be tightened. Good work McB.







