I think you've built a good foundation for the two cops for sure, but a little more flavor wouldn't hurt.

I think in this situation you could have a quick, effective cascade of breaking tone. First they're chummy and . Declaring they're entering, stating they have a warrant, pulling guns, etc. Then, after trying to put down the dog and being confronted by the anomaly, that tone breaks as well, and they sink into revulsion and fear.

Also, if these are supposed to be simple townie cops, the idea that the dialogue would close with  odd. Like, if they aren't Foundation, they should be far more disturbed and confused by these events. Solution seeking when confronted with the anomalous is more a Foundation response.





